line_1: Such, Asia, birth-place of proud monarchy,
Such, Asia, birth-place of proud monarchy,
line_2: Of superstitions fond, and learned vanity.

line_1: He has lost his share of the grand Monarchy,
line_2: And vainly lifts his forked Trident high.

line_1: When lo! the summit ends in monarchy.
line_2: Higher the pile arose, and still more high,
And wisest moderns yield to me
